WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Kaleido' is a game where you try to match 50 kaleidoscopic
patterns of variable sizes and shapes.

  Each pattern you have to match is represented by a small drawing
located at the upper right in the window. To play, click on any
tile in the main board, then, the game makes a clockwise rotation
of the following 4 tiles: the tile located on the upper left of
the board, the tile located on the upper row in the same column
from where you clicked, the leftmost tile on the same row you
clicked and the tile you clicked. Here's an example:

   a..b            c..a   Note: The spaces marked
   ....     -=>    ....         by "." are ignored
   ....            ....         in this example.
   c..d            d..b         
      ^
      ^
      Tile clicked

  Obviously, you cannot click on a tile located on the leftmost
column or on the uppermost row...

  Try to solve all the 50 game levels in the least amount of moves
possible...

  Have fun!

